channel.title: A few questions
channel.description: I've just started coding private servers, and have 3 sources that i really like. The first source is a 317, the second source is a 525 and the third source is a 474. What i don't understand is what 317, 525 and 474 mean/stand for. What's the difference between the three? I know i probably sound stupid, but i'm new to all of this. Can anybody help?

item.title: A few questions
item.dc:creator: @Basix Basix
item.description:
@Basix wrote:

[quote=“Flame_, post:2, topic:480699”][quote author=Basix link=topic=598936.msg4210826#msg4210826 date=1359510561]
I’ve just started coding private servers, and have 3 sources that i really like. The first source is a 317, the second source is a 525 and the third source is a 474. What i don’t understand is what 317, 525 and 474 mean/stand for. What’s the difference between the three? I know i probably sound stupid, but i’m new to all of this. Can anybody help?
[/quote]
The protocol/revision number. You can read about some protocol here: Click me.
Also, you don’t sound stupid in the least. At least you bother to ask some questions about what the protocols are instead of jumping straight into a 718 (more recent RuneScape revision), like most of the newcomers here who don’t even know what a string is.[/quote]

Thank-you for your post. This was extremely useful.
